<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well I mainly play a SK and I've found with my pets that giving them 2 2-handers will make them do more damage.  I don't notice with low damage weapons.  But with 10+ damage weapons they hit harder.  I have never noticed it slow them down at all either.  But those are heavy to carry around.  With necros pets, which are about the same level as the mob, procs will stick.  So any weapon with a proc will work nicely.  Gnoll whips are liked by many because they proc stun.  Also daggers of dropping (proc str debuff) just because they are common and easy to get.  And cheap weapon that procs works to your advantage though.  I have seen many necros who favor fine steel rapiers but I never thought they helped much.  I hope this helps some.  <p>

Just my observations.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
